The word modulo is a mathematical term related to division.  Two integers are equal modulo n if they have the same remainder when divided by n.  For example 2 = 12 = 22 = 32 modulo 10.  The term is also relevent to computer science.  '''Modulo arithmetic''' is arithmetic on the group formed by the choice of a constant n and the set of integers with the convention two integers are equal if and only if they are equal modulo n.